Create a program that calculates the sum of the digits of a number. The program should
accept an integer 'n' as input.
Sample Input: 12345
Sample Output: 15
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main {
public static void main(String[] args) {
Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
System.out.println("Enter a number");
int n=scan.nextInt();
CalculateSum c1 = new CalculateSum();
c1.calculateSumOfDigits(n);
}
}
public class CalculateSum {
public void calculateSumOfDigits(int n)
{
int sum=0;
while(n>0)
{
int ld=n%10;
sum=sum+ld;
n=n/10;
}
System.out.println("Sum of digits is "+sum);
}
}
